Tier-1 template surfaces that are deterministic on any machine (DESIGN §5.5/§5.7): the
remote-confirmation refusal under --no-input, a malformed ref, and `new --update` with no
tracked template. These never touch the network or the dev host; the git-backed render /
3-way-merge paths are covered by the hermetic integration tests (LOCAL fixture repos).

A REMOTE template under --no-input without --yes REFUSES at the §5.7 confirmation gate
(RK0403, exit 3) — it never silently fetches/builds, and never falls back to the default.

```
$ rackabel new x --no-input --template gh:owner/repo
? 3
  Resolving template gh:owner/repo…
This is a REMOTE template — unreviewed third-party code.
  source:  gh:owner/repo
  fetch:   https://github.com/owner/repo
  warning: `new` will fetch this repo AND run its build configuration with your
           full privileges (scaffold-time code execution). Only proceed if you
           trust the source.
error: remote template `gh:owner/repo` needs confirmation, but --no-input forbids the prompt [RK0403]
  --> gh:owner/repo
  help: pass --yes to consent to fetching AND building this third-party template in a script, or use the built-in default / a local path instead
(run `rackabel explain RK0403` for details)

```

A malformed `--template` ref is a usage error (exit 2), caught before any work.

```
$ rackabel new x --no-input --template gh:owner
? 2
error: `gh:owner` is not a valid template reference [RK0101]
  --> gh:owner
  help: use gh:owner/repo[@ref], @scope/name, or a local path
(run `rackabel explain RK0101` for details)

```

A `@scope/name` ref is accepted + classified, but npm-registry resolution is out of scope
for 0.4 — a clear not-yet-supported frame (RK0402), never a half-implementation.

```
$ rackabel new x --no-input --template @acme/starter
? 3
  Resolving template @acme/starter…
error: scoped templates like `@acme/starter` are not supported yet [RK0402]
  --> @acme/starter
  help: 0.4 resolves gh:owner/repo[@ref] and local paths; for a scoped package, point --template at its GitHub repo (gh:owner/repo) or a local checkout instead
(run `rackabel explain RK0402` for details)

```

`new --update` in a directory that was not scaffolded from a tracked template is a clear
"nothing to update" (RK0402, exit 3) — never a silent re-scaffold.

```
$ rackabel new --update --no-input
? 3
error: this project has no .rackabel-template to update from [RK0402]
  --> [..]
  help: `new --update` re-runs the template that scaffolded a project; this directory was not created from a tracked template (no .rackabel-template present)
(run `rackabel explain RK0402` for details)

```
